 given liquid for a known value of $g$, in that the resulting\nMorton number becomes constant, thereby leaving $Bo$ as the only relevant\nparameter. The computed function $We_c(Bo)$ for a water jet under Earth gravity\nis shown to be consistent with the experimental results of Clanet \\& Lasheras\n(J. Fluid Mech. vol. 383, 1999, p. 307).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Dec 2019 07:07:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-05"}
